# Privacy & compliance-oriented data

- **Minimize** fields collected and retained; define retention and deletion paths when building features.
- **Separate** roles for access to PII vs operational metrics; avoid “admin can see everything” without policy.
- **Logging**: No PII/secrets in logs; tokenize or hash identifiers if diagnostics require correlation.
- **Cross-border / lawful basis**: If the feature implies regulated data, **ask** which jurisdictions and policies apply before guessing.

Map data flows (ingress → processing → storage → egress) when touching personal or sensitive data.
